==Entities==

'''Telephone''' is the only one whose description can be completed for sure at this level. One doesn't know anything or nearly anything about the Telephone because it's almost impossible to enter the level. Not many tests have been conducted, and in all of them the same sounds always were heard when attempting to receive the call:

*Despairing, breathy whisper.
*Soft weeping and laughter in the background.
*A relative crying and Screaming your name.

The Telephone doesn't answer any questions, nor does anything change about what it does say. No one knows if the voice belongs to something living or if it just says the same thing a million times. Little is known about the Telephone.

The Telephone is a grey landline, slightly smaller, with a retro aesthetic. It has the feel of being constructed of well-worn old plastic, yet the finish is strangely rough to the finger. It is perpetually dusted with a thin coating as if it hasn't been answered in years.

==Colonies & Outposts==

Since the level is affected by the [[Phenomenon 15]] effect, it is impossible to establish colonies or bases.

==Entrances==

*Rarely, random noclipping may bring you here.

*Falling into the void of [[The Balcony|the Balcony]] may lead one here.
==Exits==

*So far, the only way out of the level is by exiting through a window of the house, which could lead to [[Level 9]], [[Level 85]], or [[Level 560]].


